WEBVTT

00:24.342 --> 00:27.592
(peaceful organ music)

00:34.730 --> 00:38.063
(melancholy jazz music)

03:09.981 --> 03:10.814
- Stop it.

03:18.372 --> 03:19.204
Stop.

03:21.939 --> 03:22.909
(grunts)

03:22.909 --> 03:24.880
(screams)

03:24.880 --> 03:25.713
No!

03:25.713 --> 03:28.046
No! (yelps)

03:33.376 --> 03:35.376
(pants)

03:39.656 --> 03:44.656
(birds tweet)
(distant dog barks)

03:52.911 --> 03:54.911
(sighs)

04:14.694 --> 04:16.694
(sighs)

04:22.292 --> 04:25.042
(lighter flicks)

04:46.025 --> 04:48.108
(sniffs)

04:49.393 --> 04:52.226
(plastic rustles)

05:23.973 --> 05:26.223
(brushing)

05:29.741 --> 05:32.574
(glove box slams)

05:33.563 --> 05:36.396
(breathes deeply)

05:40.732 --> 05:43.732
(suspenseful music)

05:48.993 --> 05:51.030
(screams)

05:51.030 --> 05:51.947
God damnit!

06:08.646 --> 06:10.646
(sighs)

06:35.201 --> 06:37.232
- Get out of the car!
(tense music)

06:37.232 --> 06:41.469
- Fuck out!
- Shit, shit! (screams)

06:41.469 --> 06:43.719
- Get out!
- Get out, freak!

06:46.009 --> 06:46.927
- Get out!

06:46.927 --> 06:49.687
- Stop it!
- Get out of your car, freak!

06:49.687 --> 06:51.238
- Leave me alone!

06:51.238 --> 06:53.558
- You kids! Leave that man alone!

06:53.558 --> 06:54.709
- [Josh] Fuck you, lady!

06:54.709 --> 06:56.279
- Okay!
- What's wrong with you?

06:56.279 --> 06:58.446
- Get the hell outta here!

07:03.108 --> 07:05.709
(Harold pants)

07:05.709 --> 07:07.938
(knocks)

07:07.938 --> 07:09.520
Hal?

07:09.520 --> 07:10.353
It's me.

07:12.370 --> 07:14.469
- Are they gone?
- Yeah.

07:14.469 --> 07:17.052
(Harold pants)

07:18.869 --> 07:23.307
- Thanks, Miss Rita. I
thought I was gonna die.

07:23.307 --> 07:25.599
- Sorry about that, Hal.

07:25.599 --> 07:29.529
These little bastards,
they out of control.

07:29.529 --> 07:31.707
(Harold sighs)

07:31.707 --> 07:33.741
You know, you wasn't nothin' like that

07:33.741 --> 07:36.359
when you was a kid, Hal.

07:36.359 --> 07:39.128
You was the sweetest little boy.

07:39.128 --> 07:42.347
Your momma was so proud of you.

07:42.347 --> 07:45.804
She move in here with you
kids, fix up that old house,

07:45.804 --> 07:50.804
said she was gonna meal-you-ate
the neighborhood. (chuckles)

07:51.928 --> 07:56.261
And I told her she ain't
had nothin' to worry about.

07:58.900 --> 08:02.619
You okay, Hal? You don't look good.

08:02.619 --> 08:05.109
- I'm sorry. I'm, I'm fine.

08:05.109 --> 08:05.942
I'm okay.

08:07.027 --> 08:08.937
- You got a list for me?

08:08.937 --> 08:10.270
- [Harold] Yeah.

08:15.459 --> 08:18.660
- I don't see no cold drinks on here.

08:18.660 --> 08:21.900
You want me to bring you some
of them orange ones you like?

08:21.900 --> 08:23.238
- Yes, please.

08:23.238 --> 08:25.919
- All right, I'll be back with this later.

08:25.919 --> 08:27.419
- [Harold] Thanks.

08:52.128 --> 08:55.128
(muffled trickling)

09:08.378 --> 09:11.128
(urine splashes)

09:33.420 --> 09:36.503
(somber piano music)

09:41.400 --> 09:44.038
- [Jacob] You're not my real dad!

09:44.038 --> 09:44.880
- Shut the fuck up.

09:44.880 --> 09:48.388
Don't you ever talk to me that way!

09:48.388 --> 09:50.598
Oh, come on, big man.

09:50.598 --> 09:52.107
Do it.

09:52.107 --> 09:53.638
Oh, give me an excuse!

09:53.638 --> 09:55.798
- [Josh] All I said is that
you're not my real dad.

09:55.798 --> 09:57.768
- [Randy] No, you're damn right I'm not.

09:57.768 --> 09:59.158
- He probably deserves it.

09:59.158 --> 09:59.991
- He left!

10:00.917 --> 10:02.787
He doesn't care about you.

10:02.787 --> 10:06.257
When your mom's not here,
that means I'm in charge.

10:06.257 --> 10:08.397
Oh and now you're gonna cry?

10:08.397 --> 10:10.367
(chuckles) Jesus Christ.

10:10.367 --> 10:11.534
Cry, cry, cry!

10:12.599 --> 10:13.599
What a baby.

10:15.836 --> 10:18.086
Get the hell out of my way.

10:20.218 --> 10:22.635
(door slams)

10:48.196 --> 10:51.113
(handbrake clicks)

11:01.618 --> 11:04.877
(Harold sniffs)

11:04.877 --> 11:07.877
(suspenseful music)

11:32.517 --> 11:34.151
- Hey!

11:34.151 --> 11:36.318
Is there someone in there?

11:37.750 --> 11:39.918
Please exit the vehicle, sir.

11:39.918 --> 11:41.790
- [Harold] Why?

11:41.790 --> 11:43.458
(knocks)

11:43.458 --> 11:45.375
- Roll the window down.

11:46.405 --> 11:48.546
- What do you want?
- Roll it down.

11:48.546 --> 11:50.796
- God damn police officers.

11:52.296 --> 11:55.596
Always harassin' people
who ain't doin' nothin'.

11:55.596 --> 11:58.037
- Please just leave me alone!
- Roll it down!

11:58.037 --> 11:58.870
- Officer!

12:00.757 --> 12:02.608
- Ma'am, I need you to stay back.

12:02.608 --> 12:05.668
- Listen to me, god damnit.

12:05.668 --> 12:06.501
(radio bleeps)

12:06.501 --> 12:07.378
- I'm gonna need backup over here

12:07.378 --> 12:09.475
at Beinvenue and Tupaneaux.

12:09.475 --> 12:11.676
- You don't need no backup.

12:11.676 --> 12:13.087
- [Dispatch] Roger that.
Backup's on the way.

12:13.087 --> 12:16.239
- This man ain't right in the head.

12:16.239 --> 12:19.766
He's been locked in that car for months.

12:19.766 --> 12:22.183
Please, just cut him a break.

12:23.408 --> 12:25.075
I looks out for him.

12:25.968 --> 12:28.148
- [Harold] Yeah, please
just leave me alone.

12:28.148 --> 12:30.107
I'm not hurting anyone.

12:30.107 --> 12:32.366
- What do you mean you "look out for him"?

12:32.366 --> 12:36.283
- His papa died and it
mess him up in the head.

12:37.864 --> 12:40.836
He's scared to get out the car.

12:40.836 --> 12:41.747
- Just go away.

12:41.747 --> 12:45.108
- When I first found him, he
was in there for five days,

12:45.108 --> 12:47.275
with no food and no water.

12:48.234 --> 12:49.651
He's almost dead.

12:51.868 --> 12:55.683
I promised his momma I
would take care of him.

12:55.683 --> 12:57.148
- Just go, dude.

12:57.148 --> 12:58.805
- [Willie] How long has he been in there?

12:58.805 --> 13:02.555
- I don't know. Five months, four months?

13:02.555 --> 13:04.853
- And you take care of him?

13:04.853 --> 13:06.410
- Yeah.

13:06.410 --> 13:07.243
I do.

13:09.370 --> 13:10.423
(radio bleeps)

13:10.423 --> 13:14.002
- Listen, cancel that backup. False alarm.

13:14.002 --> 13:16.271
- [Dispatch] 10-4, canceling backup.

13:16.271 --> 13:17.271
- All right.

13:18.945 --> 13:22.171
Look, I'm glad you take care of him,

13:22.171 --> 13:24.451
but it's illegal to live
in your car in this parish.

13:24.451 --> 13:26.111
He's got to go.

13:26.111 --> 13:29.402
And you can't just move
the car down the street.

13:29.402 --> 13:31.290
You're gonna have to get him some help.

13:31.290 --> 13:34.410
- [Rita] I'm doing the best I can.

13:34.410 --> 13:36.651
- My hands are tied.

13:36.651 --> 13:38.151
Y'all got 14 days.

13:39.903 --> 13:40.736
- Mm-hm.

13:44.202 --> 13:45.035
Hal!

13:48.733 --> 13:50.733
Look at this he gave us.

13:57.538 --> 13:59.446
He say 14 days. That's it.

13:59.446 --> 14:01.759
- I can't! I can't leave!

14:01.759 --> 14:03.859
- I know, baby, you ain't
doing nothing wrong,

14:03.859 --> 14:06.442
but he say you can't stay here.

14:14.390 --> 14:16.390
(sighs)

14:22.572 --> 14:25.322
(objects rattle)

14:30.880 --> 14:33.481
- [Harold] Shit. God damnit, kid.

14:33.481 --> 14:35.201
(pants)

14:35.201 --> 14:38.342
- What did that cop want?
- Leave me alone!

14:38.342 --> 14:42.842
Get the fuck outta here, kid! (pants)

14:51.014 --> 14:54.097
Fucking kid. (pants)

14:57.119 --> 14:59.952
(breathes deeply)

15:03.864 --> 15:05.683
(crickets chirp)

15:05.683 --> 15:09.350
(Rico whistles melodically)

15:12.954 --> 15:13.787
- Hey!

15:15.594 --> 15:16.935
(knocks)

15:16.935 --> 15:18.404
Har-Har.

15:18.404 --> 15:19.321
It's Ri-Ri!

15:20.604 --> 15:22.465
How you been, man?

15:22.465 --> 15:24.673
- [Harold] I've been all
right, man. How you doin'?

15:24.673 --> 15:25.756
- Doin' well.

15:27.382 --> 15:30.522
What you been getting into?
- Ah, nothin'.

15:30.522 --> 15:33.715
Damn kids were over here
earlier, beating on my car.

15:33.715 --> 15:36.622
Scared me half to fuckin' death.

15:36.622 --> 15:39.035
- We were just as bad when we were kids.

15:39.035 --> 15:42.425
We used to terrorize this
neighborhood. (chuckles)

15:42.425 --> 15:43.425
Beer?
- Sure.

15:46.155 --> 15:48.572
(can hisses)

15:49.876 --> 15:52.502
- Plus a cop came by, said
they're gonna tow my car.

15:52.502 --> 15:55.126
- We heard. That's why we came by.

15:55.126 --> 15:57.274
- "We"?
- Billy's coming.

15:57.274 --> 16:00.095
He should be here any second now.

16:00.095 --> 16:03.365
Can't we just pull it up the street?

16:03.365 --> 16:04.809
- Nah, they gave me a tow summons.

16:04.809 --> 16:05.967
Says I gotta get it off the street.

16:05.967 --> 16:08.759
They own the whole fuckin' thing.

16:08.759 --> 16:12.080
- I don't know anyone around
this neighborhood anymore.

16:12.080 --> 16:14.640
Did Miss Rita check with the neighbors?

16:14.640 --> 16:18.549
- Yeah, she asked a while
back. Everyone said no.

16:18.549 --> 16:19.977
They don't want a broke-down
car in their yard,

16:19.977 --> 16:23.069
much less a guy living in it.
(Rico chuckles)

16:23.069 --> 16:23.986
- I get it.

16:25.510 --> 16:27.843
How are you feeling tonight?

16:29.248 --> 16:32.539
- Jesus, man. Are you fucking serious?

16:32.539 --> 16:34.068
Intervention bullsh-

16:34.068 --> 16:35.480
- Hey! Come on, man!

16:35.480 --> 16:37.867
Hey, I'm not gonna go anywhere!

16:37.867 --> 16:40.858
- What's up, man?
- Hey, what's up, buddy?

16:40.858 --> 16:43.691
He, uh, just rolled up his window.

16:44.527 --> 16:46.419
- (scoffs) Well, I thought
I told you to wait for me?

16:46.419 --> 16:47.989
Hey, Harold.
(knocks)

16:47.989 --> 16:49.937
- I didn't say anything.
(Billy sighs)

16:49.937 --> 16:50.770
- It's me.

16:51.847 --> 16:54.679
Come on, man. Roll down the window.

16:54.679 --> 16:56.697
(Harold sighs)

16:56.697 --> 16:58.747
Hey, well, I'm not leaving.

16:58.747 --> 17:02.560
- [Harold] Why can't
you assholes understand?

17:02.560 --> 17:04.577
- Well, we're just
gonna sit here and talk,

17:04.577 --> 17:07.148
have a few drinks and, uh...

17:07.148 --> 17:08.498
I don't know, if you feel comfortable,

17:08.498 --> 17:12.498
maybe you can hop out and
sit with us for a bit, huh?

17:12.498 --> 17:13.498
- Yeah, man.

17:14.656 --> 17:16.419
Come on, Har-Har.

17:16.419 --> 17:18.419
Be a puss-puss, Har-Har.

17:21.458 --> 17:22.375
Here he is.

17:23.678 --> 17:24.511
Aww.

17:26.630 --> 17:28.888
Come on, man.
- Hey, hey.

17:28.888 --> 17:32.209
Hey, I talked to Bonny. She's
coming in town tomorrow.

17:32.209 --> 17:35.218
She's worried about you. We all are.

17:35.218 --> 17:38.599
- [Harold] You think I would...
Y'all still don't get it!

17:38.599 --> 17:41.682
- [Rico] That's why we brought you...

17:43.011 --> 17:43.844
This.

17:45.899 --> 17:47.690
- [Billy] Yeah, come on, man,
with the tow truck coming,

17:47.690 --> 17:49.357
it's Hail Mary time.

17:50.481 --> 17:51.840
It's worth a shot.

17:51.840 --> 17:53.019
- [Rico] And talking about shots,

17:53.019 --> 17:55.686
I'm gonna serve you one, Harold!

18:05.173 --> 18:06.006
Thank you.

18:17.229 --> 18:18.229
- To family.

18:19.107 --> 18:20.107
- To family.

18:27.114 --> 18:29.486
(chuckles)

18:29.486 --> 18:30.319
Another.

18:34.269 --> 18:35.936
To tres good amigos.

18:37.468 --> 18:38.687
Salud.

18:38.687 --> 18:39.520
- Salud.

18:43.134 --> 18:46.175
(Harold coughs)
(Rico chuckles)

18:46.175 --> 18:48.675
- You're out of practice, huh?

18:50.215 --> 18:51.682
(chuckles) Do you guys remember

18:51.682 --> 18:54.273
when we streaked down to Melanie's house?

18:54.273 --> 18:56.123
(laughs)

18:56.123 --> 18:57.206
- Yeah, I do.

18:58.083 --> 19:01.085
I had the biggest crush on her, man.

19:01.085 --> 19:04.165
What was that, like 20 years ago?

19:04.165 --> 19:04.998
- 16.

19:06.104 --> 19:08.643
Come on, let's do some more.

19:08.643 --> 19:09.633
- Oh!

19:09.633 --> 19:10.466
Okay.

19:10.466 --> 19:11.813
- [Harold] Let me pour.

19:11.813 --> 19:13.896
- The Har-Har is pouring.

19:17.973 --> 19:20.890
Oh, oh! (chuckles)

19:22.070 --> 19:22.903
Okay.

19:27.133 --> 19:28.133
- To trying.

19:29.008 --> 19:32.341
- (chuckles) To trying.

19:35.295 --> 19:37.434
(grunts)

19:37.434 --> 19:38.934
- [Jenny] Asshole!

19:41.515 --> 19:43.663
- [Rico] That asshole is beating
up Jenny and Jacob again.

19:43.663 --> 19:46.165
- Jesus, is she still with that loser?

19:46.165 --> 19:48.170
- [Harold] He probably deserves it.

19:48.170 --> 19:49.751
- Who? The kid?

19:49.751 --> 19:52.209
- Well, he's always over
here, fucking with me.

19:52.209 --> 19:53.512
Him and his piece of shit friends

19:53.512 --> 19:56.821
were beating on my car earlier,
scared the shit outta me.

19:56.821 --> 19:57.654
- Yeah...

19:59.111 --> 20:03.430
(chuckles) You know I care about you.

20:03.430 --> 20:07.570
I gave the kids a couple
of bucks to do it.

20:07.570 --> 20:08.460
- Fuck?

20:08.460 --> 20:11.531
- I thought that if you
would get mad enough,

20:11.531 --> 20:13.560
you would get out of the fucking car!

20:13.560 --> 20:14.909
(Rico and Billy laugh)

20:14.909 --> 20:16.009
- Classic, man.

20:16.009 --> 20:19.888
- It was made out of pure
love. You know I love you.

20:19.888 --> 20:22.091
(blows kiss and chuckles)

20:22.091 --> 20:25.571
- Get the hell outta here!
- Scared me shitless.

20:25.571 --> 20:26.988
That's fucked up.

20:27.890 --> 20:31.223
- Get the hell outta here!
- I'm leaving.

20:32.662 --> 20:33.495
- Go!

20:34.691 --> 20:37.108
(car starts)

20:40.461 --> 20:41.294
- Yeah!

20:44.902 --> 20:46.589
- Can I get a hug?

20:46.589 --> 20:49.749
I wanna give my big brother
a hug. Come on, hey.

20:49.749 --> 20:50.582
I want in.

20:51.961 --> 20:53.632
Come on! Come on, man-

20:53.632 --> 20:54.953
- [Harold] You're not coming in here, man.

20:54.953 --> 20:57.813
- Come on, Harold, let me in.
- Hey, come on, guys.

20:57.813 --> 20:58.976
- No!
- Guys.

20:58.976 --> 21:01.745
- Harold, let me in the car.
- No, you're not coming in!

21:01.745 --> 21:04.905
- That's pretty loud, guys.
It's public disturbance.

21:04.905 --> 21:06.626
- Let me in, now.

21:06.626 --> 21:08.533
- No.
- Yes, open the door!

21:08.533 --> 21:09.994
- I'm not opening the fucking door.

21:09.994 --> 21:11.288
You are not getting in here.

21:11.288 --> 21:13.456
- [Billy] Hey. (knocks) Come on, man!

21:13.456 --> 21:15.836
- Stop it!
- Open the door, right now!

21:15.836 --> 21:17.035
- [Rico] We were just having fun!

21:17.035 --> 21:19.664
- This is between me
and my brother. Shut up.

21:19.664 --> 21:21.766
Come on, dude. Open the window.

21:21.766 --> 21:23.066
Open this door, or I will break it.

21:23.066 --> 21:26.668
- Oh, come on, man.
- Hey. (knocks)

21:26.668 --> 21:28.639
- I'm on probation,
guys. Have a good night.

21:28.639 --> 21:30.224
- Good, go.
- Dude, just fucking-

21:30.224 --> 21:32.547
- Yeah, that's what
I'm doing. I'm leaving.

21:32.547 --> 21:33.380
- Harold.

21:35.677 --> 21:38.704
- You can't come in here, Billy.

21:38.704 --> 21:42.974
- So what's it gonna be,
smashed window or me inside?

21:42.974 --> 21:44.332
One.

21:44.332 --> 21:45.743
Two.

21:45.743 --> 21:47.743
Three. Come on, open up.

21:49.669 --> 21:50.648
See?

21:50.648 --> 21:52.875
Now that wasn't so hard.

21:52.875 --> 21:55.156
(grunts) I want a hug from my brother!

21:55.156 --> 21:56.996
It's just garbage, Harold.
- Stop it, Billy!

21:56.996 --> 21:59.189
Fuck, dude!
- It's just garbage!

21:59.189 --> 22:01.106
- Is this garbage? Huh?

22:01.997 --> 22:04.497
(Billy sighs)

22:06.316 --> 22:07.816
- [Billy] Oh, wow.

22:08.727 --> 22:10.810
This is, uh, so long ago.

22:11.717 --> 22:15.589
- It's 20 years, five months and 18 days.

22:15.589 --> 22:16.422
- Yeah.

22:18.148 --> 22:19.770
Yeah, that was fucked up.

22:19.770 --> 22:22.858
- [Harold] You weren't here.

22:22.858 --> 22:23.941
- I miss her.

22:24.900 --> 22:25.733
I grieved.

22:28.351 --> 22:29.857
- He killed her.

22:29.857 --> 22:33.459
I was sitting right here
and I couldn't do anything.

22:33.459 --> 22:34.940
I couldn't save her.
- What could you do?

22:34.940 --> 22:37.273
You were a fucking kid, man.

22:42.309 --> 22:44.788
- You fuckin' asshole.

22:44.788 --> 22:46.131
- [Billy] He is still our dad.

22:46.131 --> 22:48.001
- That piece of shit will never be my dad.

22:48.001 --> 22:49.937
- She was having an affair, Harold!

22:49.937 --> 22:51.730
It was tearing the family apart!

22:51.730 --> 22:53.098
- Fuck you, dude!
- Oh, come on!

22:53.098 --> 22:57.680
I come down here every weekend
after work to come see you!

22:57.680 --> 23:00.499
I'm trying to figure out a way
to help you! What can we do?

23:00.499 --> 23:01.831
- Don't you think if
I had somewhere to go,

23:01.831 --> 23:03.961
that I'd already fuckin' be-
- Fuck this, man!

23:03.961 --> 23:05.879
I mean, stop feeling sorry for yourself!

23:05.879 --> 23:07.559
There's nothing wrong with you!

23:07.559 --> 23:09.058
Grow up! Be a man!

23:09.058 --> 23:11.281
- Fuck you! Get the fuck out of my car!

23:11.281 --> 23:13.511
- Oh, man, you know what?
I'll tear you out of this car!

23:13.511 --> 23:15.049
Get over here!
- Fuck you, man!

23:15.049 --> 23:17.289
Get the fuck off me!
(Billy groans)

23:17.289 --> 23:18.921
Leave me the fuck alone, dude.

23:18.921 --> 23:21.208
- You want me to leave you
alone? Well, fine, you know what?

23:21.208 --> 23:22.400
When they come and get you,

23:22.400 --> 23:24.032
you will wish that I
was here to protect you!

23:24.032 --> 23:25.701
- Yeah.
- But you know what?

23:25.701 --> 23:29.129
Maybe that's where you
need to be. Fuck you!

23:29.129 --> 23:30.391
(car door slams)
